                                      Flow Control / Control Flow
                                      ---------------------------

Flow control describe the order in which statements will be executed at runtime.

                 
                                      Control Flow
                                      -------------

Conditional Statements             Iterative Statements               Transfer Statements

1.if                                1.for                             1.break
2.else                              2.while                           2.continue
3.if-elif-else                                                        3.pass


Conditional Statements:-
-----------------------

It's block of code that is execute only condition purpose.

1. if:-

syntax:-

if condiition:
	statement-1
	statement-2
	------------
	------------

if condition is true then statements will be executed otherwise not.




Indentation:- 

Indentation refers to the spaces at the block of code beginning of a code line. Python uses indentation to indicate a block of code. 

Wherein other programming the indentation in code is for readability only,but in python the indentation is very important.


Ex:-

name = input("Enter your name:-")

if name == 'Vishal':
    print("Hi",name,"Good morning")

 Output:-

 Enter your name:-Vishal
Hi Vishal Good morning

------------------------------------------------
name = input("Enter your name:-")
age = eval(input("Enter your age:-"))

if name == 'Vishal' and age == 26:
    print("Hi",name,"Good morning")
    print('Vishal age is:-',age)

out:-

Enter your name:-Vishal
Enter your age:-26
Hi Vishal Good morning
Vishal age is:- 26



Out of indentation:-

name = input("Enter your name:-")
age = eval(input("Enter your age:-"))

if name == 'Vishal':
    print("Hi",name,"Good morning")
print('Hi all of you')

output:-
Enter your name:-bunty
Hi all of you



if-else:-
-------

Syntax:-

if condition:
	statement

else:
	statement

if condition is true then statement of if will be executed otherwise else statement will be executed.

name = input("Enter your name:-")

if name == 'Vishal':
    print('Hi Vishal Good mornging')
else:
    print('Hi Guys Good morning')



3. if-elif-else:-
-----------------
Based on condtional the corresponding statement will be excuted.\

syntax:-

if condition:
	statement

elif condition:
	statement-1

elif condition:-
	statement-3

else:
	statement-4


ex:-
soft_drinks = input("Enter your choice of drink:-")
if soft_drinks == "Thumpsop":
    print("it's best drink")
elif soft_drinks == "7up":
    print("it's better")
elif soft_drinks == "slice":
    print("craving more")
else:
    print("lembu pani is best option")


Note:-

1.else part is always optional.
2.if
3.if-else
4.if-elif
5.if-elif-else
6.elif----------wrong
7.else----------wrong
8.elif-else-----wrong

9.There is no switch statement in python.

Q-1.WAP to find biggest of given 2 numbers?

n1 = eval(input("Enter first number:-"))
n2 = eval(input("Enter second number:-"))

if n1>n2:
    print("Biigest no is:-",n1)
else:
    print("Biggest no is:-",n2)


Q-2.WAP to find biggest of given 3 numbers?

n1=eval(input('enter first number:'))
n2=eval(input('enter second number:'))
n3=eval(input('enter third number:'))
if n1>n2 and n1>n3:
    print("1st number is greater")
elif n2>n3:
    print("2nd number is greater")
else:
    print("third number is greater")



Ternary Operator:- special condition of if/single line conditional statement

synatx:-

variable = statement_1 if condition else statement_2

if condition is True then firstvalue will be considered else secondvalue will be considered.

a = 10
b = 20

x = a if a>b else b
print(x)


